\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Authorization Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Authorization requirements for maintenance and repair activity are differentiated by asset support classification as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
IT-Managed Assets
\series default
:
 No vendor,
 contractor,
 or non-IT Department personnel shall perform technical work on an IT-Managed asset without explicit written IT Director authorization.
 IT Department personnel initiating scheduled maintenance on IT-Managed assets shall obtain authorization in accordance with the IT-initiated work order requirements of 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.3:
 routine maintenance tasks may be authorized by the assigned technician in accordance with their defined role authority under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
;
 non-routine or significant maintenance tasks shall be authorized by the Assistant IT Director or IT Director prior to work commencement.
 When maintenance activity is performed on systems that process,
 store,
 or transmit CJI,
 the IT Department escort shall be fully cleared and technically qualified to supervise the specific maintenance activity being performed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
IT-Supported Assets
\series default
:
 Vendor involvement in maintenance on an IT-Supported asset that falls within the contracted support scope shall be authorized by the Assistant IT Director.
 Vendor involvement outside the contracted support scope shall require IT Director authorization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Vendor-Managed Assets
\series default
:
 Vendor personnel performing maintenance within their exclusive support domain do not require ECIO authorization.
 The IT Department's obligations for Vendor-Managed maintenance events are limited to access facilitation in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 physical escort in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 and work order documentation of coordination activity in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All maintenance activity shall be documented in a work order prior to commencement,
 except as provided under the emergency exception defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The authorizing official and the basis for authorization shall be recorded in the work order before work begins.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Remote Maintenance Session Controls
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All remote maintenance sessions on County IT systems shall be directly observed by the IT Department personnel assigned to the work order for the duration of the session.
 Unmonitored remote access —
 including desktop sharing,
 screen sharing,
 or any remote control session initiated by any party —
 is strictly prohibited regardless of asset classification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Remote maintenance sessions shall be conducted exclusively through County-approved secure remote access mechanisms in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Remote session logging and audit trail obligations are governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Upon completion of remote maintenance,
 the IT Department personnel observing the session shall verify that the session and all associated network connections have been fully terminated before the maintenance work order is closed.
 Termination verification shall be documented in the work order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Maintenance Tool Controls
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Any maintenance tool —
 hardware,
 software,
 or firmware —
 brought onto County premises or connected remotely for maintenance purposes shall appear on the approved maintenance tool list maintained in the Knowledge Base under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No maintenance tool may be used on County systems unless it appears on that list.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Media containing diagnostic or test programs shall be inspected for malicious code before use on any County system.
 Maintenance tools brought by vendors or contractors shall be subject to the same inspection requirement as tools used by IT Department personnel.
 Tool inspection procedures are maintained in the Knowledge Base under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Prior to the removal of any vendor-supplied or contractor-supplied maintenance tool or diagnostic equipment from County facilities,
 the IT Department personnel assigned to the work order shall verify that the equipment contains no County data,
 or shall ensure the equipment is sanitized before departure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall approve the authorized maintenance tool list.
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure the list is current.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Post-Maintenance Verification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Upon completion of any maintenance or repair activity on an IT-Managed or IT-Supported asset,
 the IT Department personnel assigned to the work order shall verify that the system and all potentially affected controls are functioning correctly before the maintenance work order is closed.
 Post-maintenance verification procedures are maintained in the Knowledge Base under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Verification results shall be documented in the work order.
 A work order shall not be closed in the absence of a documented post-maintenance verification result.
\end_layout

