\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Off-Site Component Removal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
No County IT system component shall be removed from County facilities for off-site maintenance,
 repair,
 or replacement without explicit written IT Director authorization.
 The authorization shall be documented in the work order prior to removal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Prior to removal,
 the component shall be sanitized in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 to remove County data from all associated media.
 If sanitization is not technically feasible prior to removal,
 the IT Director shall authorize an alternative control,
 which shall be documented in the work order in lieu of the sanitization confirmation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The work order shall record the authorization,
 the sanitization confirmation or the authorized alternative control,
 and the chain of custody for the removed component from departure through return or disposal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Timely Maintenance for CJI-Processing Systems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Maintenance support and spare parts for system components that process,
 store,
 or transmit Criminal Justice Information (CJI) shall be obtained within the recovery time objective (RTO) and recovery point objective (RPO) defined for those systems in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.15"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 This requirement ties maintenance support availability to the existing continuity planning framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.15"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and does not create independent planning obligations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Work orders documenting maintenance and repair activity under this policy shall be retained for a minimum of three (3) calendar years after the repair is completed,
 in accordance with NRS 239.125.
\end_layout

